<paragraph blockId="4.[831,1470,509,628]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[831,970,509,533]" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[831,947,509,533]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
–
</emphasis>
Species with brown wing and brown stigma. Discal cell almost as long as basal cells. Mesonotum anteriorly shining black. Hind femur club-shaped, ventrally with spine-like bristles.
</paragraph>
